== 詞源 ==
桁架的英文truss源自約1200年時的古法文trousse，意思是「許多連結在一起東西的集合」<ref>Reif, F., [http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=truss etymonline.com] {{Wayback|url=http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=truss |date=20160304074542 }} (1965).</ref><ref>Oxford English Dictionary</ref>。truss一詞還常常用來描述由許多元件組合的物體，例如{{le|曲木|cruck}}框架<ref>Noble, Allen George. Traditional buildings a global survey of structural forms and cultural functions. London: I.B. Tauris ;, 2007. 115. ISBN 1845113055</ref><ref>Davies, Nikolas, and Erkki Jokiniemi. Dictionary of architecture and building construction. Amsterdam: Elsevier/Architectural Press, 2008. 394. ISBN 0750685026</ref>及屋頂的椽架<ref>Davies, Nikolas, and Erkki Jokiniemi. Architect's illustrated pocket dictionary. Oxford: Architectural Press, 2011. 121. ISBN 0080965377</ref><ref>Crabb, George. Universal Technological Dictionary Or Familiar Explanation of the Terms used in All Arts and Sciences...", Volume 1 London: 1823. Couples.</ref>，不過也常用來表達以下工程上的定義「桁架是由許多個別結構件組成的單一平面框架，結構件的末端互相連接，形成許多三角形，可以延伸很長的距離。」<ref>Shekhar, R. K. Chandra. Academic dictionary of civil engineering. Delhi: Isha Books, 2005. 431. ISBN 8182051908</ref>。

== 桁架的特點 ==
桁架一般（但並非一定）會包括直桿結構件，彼此以接點相連，這些接點也稱為panel points。  桁架一般（但並非一定<ref name="BeerJohnston">{{cite book|last1=Beer|first1=Ferd|last2=Johnston|first2=Russ|title=Vector Mechanics for Engineers: Statics|date=2013|publisher=McGraw-Hill|location=New York, NY|isbn=0-07-740228-6|pages=285–313|edition=10th|accessdate=17 September 2014|ref=BeerJohnston}}</ref>）會由三角形組成，因為三角形有其結構上的穩定性。三角形是最簡單只要各邊長度確定，其形狀就不會改變的幾何圖形<ref name="ricker">{{cite book | last = Ricker | first = Nathan Clifford | title = A Treat on Design and Construction of Roofs| origyear = 1912 | url = http://books.google.com/books?id=b6oJAAAAIAAJ| accessdate = 2008-08-15 | year = 1912 | publisher = J. Wiley & Sons | location = New York | pages = 12}}</ref>。相較起來，四邊形的各邊及各角都要確定才會確定其形狀。桁架中設計用來支撐的接點一般會稱為munter point。

===簡易桁架===
[[File:Trusses_008.jpg|thumb]]
[[File:Santa_croce,_navata,_capriate.JPG|thumb]]的屋頂用桁架]]
三角形就是最簡單的桁架，這類的桁架常出現在屋頂，由二根斜向的{{le|椽架|rafter}}及水平的{{le|托梁|joist}}組成一個單元<ref name="maginnis">{{cite book|last=Maginnis|first=Owen Bernard|title=Roof Framing Made Easy|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=GJdBAAAAIAAJ|accessdate=2008-08-16|edition=2nd|year=1903|publisher=The Industrial Publication Company|location=New York|pages=9|archive-date=2014-04-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140424142504/http://books.google.com/books?id=GJdBAAAAIAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>，像在[[自行車車架|自行車]]及飛機上也可以看到類似的架構。這類的桁架有形狀的穩定性，且已有方法可以分析其各部份的受力，因此由三角形組成的桁架稱為簡易桁架<ref name="hibbeler">{{cite book | last = Hibbeler | first = Russell Charles | title = Engineering Mechanics-Statics| url = https://archive.org/details/engineeringmecha0000hibb | origyear = 1974 | edition = 3rd | year = 1983 | publisher = Macmillan Publishing Co., Inc. | location = New York | isbn = 0-02-354310-8 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/engineeringmecha0000hibb/page/199 199]–224}}</ref>。<!--However, a simple truss is often defined more restrictively by demanding that it can be constructed through successive addition of pairs of members, each connected to two existing joints and to each other to form a new joint, and this definition does not require a simple truss to comprise only triangles.<ref name="BeerJohnston"/>-->像傳統由二個相鄰三角形組成的鑽石型自行車車架，就是簡易桁架的例子<ref>Wingerter, R., and Lebossiere, P., ''ME 354, Mechanics of Materials Laboratory: Structures'', University of Washington (February 2004), p.1</ref>。

===平面桁架===
平面桁架位在同一[[平面_(数学)|平面]]上<ref name="hibbeler"/>，一般會用數個平面桁架平行排列，組成屋頂及橋梁。

平面桁架的深度，也就是平面桁架上方及下方的上弦杆及下弦杆之間的距離，是桁架之所以成為經濟耐用的結構的原因。實心的[[梁_(结构)|梁]]或是[[樑|樑]]不論是重量或是成本，都比相同強度的桁架要貴。[[跨度|跨度]]相同時，若桁架的深度越深，其上弦杆及下弦杆所需的材料越少，但垂直杆及對角線杆需要的材料會增加。因此若深度最佳化，桁架的成本也可以節省<ref name="meriman">{{cite book|last=Merriman|first=Mansfield|title=American Civil Engineers' Pocket Book|origyear=192|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=AUVIAAAAIAAJ|accessdate=2008-08-16|year=1912|publisher=J. Wiley & Sons|location=New York|pages=785|quote=The Economic Depth of a Truss is that which makes the material in a bridge a minimum.|archive-date=2013-12-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131231124136/http://books.google.com/books?id=AUVIAAAAIAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===立體桁架===
[[空間桁架|空間桁架]]是三維的框架，各杆的末端以旋轉接點相接。[[四面體|四面體]]的外形是最簡單的桁架，由六根杆組成，有四個接點<ref name="hibbeler"/>。大型的平面結構也可以用[[四面體|四面體]]組成，在大型的獨立{{le|輸電桿塔|power line pylon}}中也有用到立體桁架。

